article.description: — Adrian Delph had 29 points as Appalachian State defeated Louisiana-Monroe 77-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Delph scores 29 to carry Appalachian St. over ULM 77-69
article.linkText: Delph scores 29 to carry Appalachian St. over ULM 77-69
article.story: BOONE, N.C. -- — Adrian Delph had 29 points as Appalachian State defeated Louisiana-Monroe 77-69 on Saturday. Donovan Gregory had 15 points and eight rebounds for the Mountaineers (7-8, 1-1 Sun Belt Conference). Michael Almonacy added 13 points and 10 assists. CJ Huntley had 12 points. Koreem Ozier had 19 points for the Warhawks (8-6, 0-2). Nika Metskhvarishvili added 17 points. Andre Jones had 14 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
